
Experimental results on whether spectral norm helps : 

version_0 : using spectral norm for inertial encoder w/o batch norm
version_1 : no spectral norm
version_2 : spectral norm only on the projection layer
version_3 : no spectral norm, using gradient clip val of "norm" of 1.0


Results : 

version_0 : very good separability
version_1 : very good separability
version_2 : poor separability 
version_3 : no separability

Conclusion : Donot use any spectral norm / gradient clipping. 